restclient-cpp
------------------------------------------
This is a simple REST client for C++. It wraps libcurl for HTTP requests.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.5-1
  libcurl-devel-7.66.0-1
  libcurl4-7.66.0-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  librestclient-cpp-devel-0.5.2-1bl1
  librestclient-cpp1-0.5.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mrtazz/restclient-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mrtazz/restclient-cpp/archive/0.5.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack restclient-cpp-0.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./restclient-cpp-0.5.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/restclient-cpp-0.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/restclient-cpp-0.5.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librestclient-cpp1-0.5.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librestclient-cpp-devel-0.5.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(restclient-cpp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/restclient-cpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/restclient-cpp/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/restclient-cpp/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/restclient-cpp/README.md

(librestclient-cpp1)
  /usr/bin/cygrestclient-cpp-1.dll

(librestclient-cpp-devel)
  /usr/include/restclient-cpp/connection.h
  /usr/include/restclient-cpp/helpers.h
  /usr/include/restclient-cpp/restclient.h
  /usr/include/restclient-cpp/version.h
  /usr/lib/librestclient-cpp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/restclient-cpp.pc

